label.value: Thymic Tumor pM1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Thymic tumor with pleural, pericardial, or distant metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Thymic Tumor pM1a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Thymic tumor with separate pleural or pericardial nodule(s). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Thymic Tumor pM1b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Thymic tumor with pulmonary intraparenchymal nodule or distant organ metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Thymic Tumor Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of a thymic tumor, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Thymic Tumor pTX TNM Finding v8

value.value: Thymic tumor in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Thymic Tumor pT0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Thymic tumor without evidence of primary tumor. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Thymic Tumor pT1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Thymic tumor which is encapsulated or extends into the mediastinal fat; may involve the mediastinal pleura. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Thymic Tumor pT1a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Thymic tumor with no mediastinal pleura involvement. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
A chromosome band present on 3p

label.value: Thymic Tumor pT1b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Thymic tumor with direct invasion of mediastinal pleura. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Thymic Tumor pT2 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Thymic tumor with direct invasion of the pericardium (either partial or full thickness). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Thymic Tumor pT3 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Thymic tumor with direct invasion into any of the following: lung, brachiocephalic vein, superior vena cava, phrenic nerve, chest wall, or extrapericardial pulmonary artery or veins. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Thymic Tumor pT4 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Thymic tumor with invasion into any of the following: aorta (ascending, arch, or descending), arch vessels, intrapericardial pulmonary artery, myocardium, trachea, esophagus. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Thymic Tumor Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of a thymic tumor, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Thymic Tumor pNX TNM Finding v8

value.value: Thymic tumor in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed.  (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Thymic Tumor pN0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Thymic tumor without regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Thymic Tumor pN1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Thymic tumor with metastasis in anterior (perithymic) lymph nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Thymic Tumor pN2 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Thymic tumor with metastasis in deep intrathoracic or cervical lymph nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Memorial Symptom Assessment Scale (MSAS) 7-12

value.value: A patient-rated questionnaire designed to evaluate the prevalence, characteristics, and distress to young children with cancer aged 7-12. This 8-question instrument was adapted from a previously-validated adult version.
A chromosome band present on 11p

label.value: Thymic Epithelial Neoplasm by AJCC v8 Stage

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of a thymic epithelial neoplasm, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system. This staging system applies to thymomas, thymic carcinomas, thymic neuroendocrine tumors, and combined thymic carcinomas. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Yesterday or Today

value.value: The time period consisting of the current day and the preceding day.

label.value: Stage I Thymic Epithelial Neoplasm AJCC v8

value.value: Stage I includes: T1a, b, N0, M0. T1a: Tumor with no mediastinal pleura involvement. T1b: Tumor with direct invasion of mediastinal pleura. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage II Thymic Epithelial Neoplasm AJCC v8

value.value: Stage II includes: T2, N0, M0. T2: Tumor with direct invasion of the pericardium (either partial or full thickness). N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Last 2 Days

value.value: The 48 hour period occurring just before the present time.

label.value: Stage III Thymic Epithelial Neoplasm AJCC v8

value.value: Stage III includes: IIIA: (T3, N0, M0); IIIB: (T4, N0, M0). T3: Tumor with direct invasion into any of the following: lung, brachiocephalic vein, superior vena cava, phrenic nerve, chest wall, or extrapericardial pulmonary artery or veins. T4: Tumor with invasion into any of the following: aorta (ascending, arch, or descending), arch vessels, intrapericardial pulmonary artery, myocardium, trachea, esophagus. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Last 2 Nights

value.value: The period of time consisting of the previous night and the night before the previous night.

label.value: Stage IIIA Thymic Epithelial Neoplasm AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIIA includes: T3, N0, M0. T3: Tumor with direct invasion into any of the following: lung, brachiocephalic vein, superior vena cava, phrenic nerve, chest wall, or extrapericardial pulmonary artery or veins. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIB Thymic Epithelial Neoplasm AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIIB includes: T4, N0, M0. T4: Tumor with invasion into any of the following: aorta (ascending, arch, or descending), arch vessels, intrapericardial pulmonary artery, myocardium, trachea, esophagus. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IV Thymic Epithelial Neoplasm AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IV includes: IVA: (Any T, N1, M0); (Any T, N0,1, M1a); IVB: (Any T, N2, M0, M1a); (Any T, Any N, M1b). N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. N1: Metastasis in anterior (perithymic) lymph nodes. N2: Metastasis in deep intrathoracic or cervical lymph nodes. M0: No distant metastasis. M1a: Separate pleural or pericardial nodule(s). M1b: Pulmonary intraparenchymal nodule or distant organ metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)
A chromosome band present on 18p

label.value: Stage IVA Thymic Epithelial Neoplasm AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IVA includes: (Any T, N1, M0); (Any T, N0,1, M1a). N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. N1: Metastasis in anterior (perithymic) lymph nodes. M0: No distant metastasis. M1a: Separate pleural or pericardial nodule(s). (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IVB Thymic Epithelial Neoplasm AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IVB includes: (Any T, N2, M0, M1a); (Any T, Any N, M1b). N2: Metastasis in deep intrathoracic or cervical lymph nodes. M0: No distant metastasis. M1a: Separate pleural or pericardial nodule(s). M1b: Pulmonary intraparenchymal nodule or distant organ metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

value.value: A response indicating that something happens or happened for a medium amount of time.

value.value: A response indicating that something is or was of a moderate amount, intensity, or duration.

label.value: More Tired Than Usual

value.value: A question about how tired an individual felt.

label.value: How Much Bothered by Being Tired

value.value: A question about how much being tired bothered or troubled an individual.

label.value: Retinoic Acid Response Element

value.value: A cis-acting transcription regulatory element.  It is bound by the retinoic acid receptors.

label.value: How Long Felt Sad

value.value: A question about how long an individual felt sad.

label.value: How Sad

value.value: A question about how sad an individual felt.

value.value: A procedure in which the location of a cancerous polyp is marked with a dye during colonoscopy, for the purpose of identifying the site for later, possible resection.

label.value: How Much Feeling Sad Bothered or Troubled You

value.value: A question about how much an individual was bothered or troubled by feeling sad.

label.value: Complete Parametrectomy

value.value: Surgical removal of the parametrial tissues.

label.value: Thymoma by AJCC v8 Stage

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of thymoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Determination of Tumor DNA Mismatch Repair Status

value.value: An assessment of the DNA mismatch repair (MMR) status of a cancerous neoplasm.

label.value: Were Itchy

value.value: A question about whether an individual feels or felt itchy.
